Tanzania Bureau of Standards (TBS) has urged building bricks manufacturers to observe quality and standards that would assure the construction of solidand strong buildings. The remarks were made by the Acting TBS Director General Johanes Maganga in Dar es Salaam yesterday,when opening the meeting building bricks manufacturers organised by TBS. “Building bricks manufacturers should make sure the materials used in bricks making are of high quality as well as observing the right ratios in mixing them,” he said mentioning some of the materials like clay, sand, cement and water. He noted the construction of a building using low quality bricks may endanger the safety of the people who are going to reside the house. Mr Maganga added that, “Building bricks manufacturers are important stakeholders in the construction sector and in making sure that the construction of houses meets the quality standards,” During the meeting, building bricks manufacturers requested TBS to visit stakeholders in their manufacturing sites to inspect and train them on making quality bricks. They asked the TBS to make arrange meetings with building bricks manufacturers to provide education on ‘marking and grades’ that are used in bricks making in the country. They also asked TBS to provide more awareness and education services on ‘frost weathering action’ which is important before buying bricks and erecting a building. Mr Maganga pledged to work closely with building bricks manufacturers to make sure that they produce high quality bricks needed in constructing solid and strong building.